-- Fed Funds Projected to Open at 0.13% to 0.17%, ICAP Says
-- B y   L i z   C a p o   M c C o r m i c k
-- 2012-06-04T11:27:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-04/fed-funds-projected-to-open-at-0-13-to-0-17-icap-says.html
Fed funds, the U.S. overnight inter-
bank lending  rate , is projected to open in a range of 0.13
percent to 0.17 percent, within the  Federal Reserve ’s target of
zero to 0.25 percent.  Fed funds closed at 0.15 percent on June 1 after trading
from 0.14 percent to 0.28 percent and averaging 0.16 percent,
ICAP Plc, the world’s largest inter-dealer broker, said in an e-
mailed statement. ICAP’s monthly average is 0.156 percent.  The central bank will acquire Treasuries maturing from June
2018 to May 2020. The purchases are the first in the Fed’s new
program to replace $400 billion of short-term debt in its
portfolio with longer-term Treasuries in an effort to reduce
borrowing costs further and counter rising risks of a recession.  The central bank plans to purchase from $4.25 billion to
$5.25 billion of securities today, according to the  New York 
Fed’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Liz Capo McCormick in New York at 
